### Example: Capture and use variables from JSON responses

### Step 1: Create a user and capture the ID
# @capture userId=id
# @capture userName=name
POST https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "username": "johndoe",
  "email": "john@example.com"
}

###

### Step 2: Create a post using the captured userId
# @capture postId=id
POST https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "My First Post",
  "body": "This is a post by {{userName}}",
  "userId": {{userId}}
}

###

### Step 3: Get user details and capture nested fields
# @capture userEmail=email
# @capture userCity=address.city
# @capture userCompany=company.name
GET https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users/1

###

### Step 4: Use all captured variables in a complex request
POST https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Post from {{userCity}}",
  "body": "Author: {{userName}} ({{userEmail}}) works at {{userCompany}}",
  "userId": {{userId}}
}

###

### Example: Capture from arrays
# @capture firstPostId=0.id
# @capture firstPostTitle=0.title
GET https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts?userId=1
